        "law_explanation": "ACL s23(2)(a) states that a term is unfair if it would cause a significant imbalance in the parties\u2019 rights and obligations arising under the contract. Allowing the Society to unilaterally determine the governing law creates such an imbalance, potentially overriding consumer protections afforded under Australian law.",
        "location": "4",
