        "justification": "The original text specifies that the agreement is governed by the laws of the Commonwealth of Australia and the State of Victoria. The changed text replaces this with governance solely determined by the Society. According to the ACL s23(2)(a), as described in the Law Explanation, a term is unfair if it creates a significant imbalance in the parties\u2019 rights and obligations. The changed text removes the consumer protections provided by Australian law by allowing the Society to unilaterally determine the governing law, which creates a significant imbalance and thus, a contradiction. While there are no direct scraped snippets to refer to, the Law Explanation clearly states a violation of ACL s23(2)(a), fulfilling the Omission Legal Contradiction criteria."
