        ],
        "law_explanation": "The case Burns v MAN Automotive (Aust) Ltd (1986) 161 CLR 653 discusses principles for the availability of remedies. The clause 'A breach of any of the promises or agreements contained herein will result in damage to the Society, and the Society shall be entitled to relief.' may be interpreted as suggesting that the society is entitled to relief without establishing irreparable harm or the inadequacy of monetary damages.",
