        "contradiction_exists": "YES",
        "justification": "The original text specifies 'irreparable and continuing damage' as a condition for certain remedies. The changed text omits this requirement, stating simply that 'damage to the Society' is sufficient for 'relief'. This omission weakens the standard required for obtaining remedies such as injunctive relief or specific performance. The Perturbation Explanation argues this could limit the remedies available and potentially violate principles of equitable relief. The Law Explanation suggests this change implies relief may be granted without establishing irreparable harm or the inadequacy of monetary damages. While Scraped Law Snippet 1 is not directly relevant, the absence of a Snippet supporting the change further reinforces the legal risk. The omission of the 'irreparable and continuing damage' requirement fundamentally alters the conditions under which the Society can seek relief, creating a contradiction."
